text: Scinax rupestris is a frog. It lives in Goi√°s in Brazil. It lives more than 1000 meters above sea level. It lives in small rivers near where there is quartzite rock in the ground. The adult male frog is 21.9 to 27.7 mm long from nose to rear end and the adult female frog is 26.7 to 31.7 mm. The iris of its eye is bright yellow. There is a small, hard spike behind the jaw. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
